From afadf116a670811a3387ed34c1e76ebef24a0c11 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: psyclyx <me@psyclyx.xyz>
Date: Thu, 2 Apr 2026 14:17:15 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] fix: use transaction path for Wayland buffer commit and
 layer setup

Android 16's front-end architecture requires buffer and layer state
changes to go through setTransactionState() rather than direct
Layer method calls. The old approach (Layer::setBuffer/setCrop)
modified mDrawingState which is no longer read by the compositor.

Changes:
- WaylandSurface: submit buffers via TransactionState with
  eBufferChanged + eCropChanged flags instead of Layer::setBuffer()
- WaylandCompositor: set z-order via TransactionState on layer
  creation to place Wayland surfaces above app layers
- WaylandCompositor: add eNoColorFill flag to prevent black
  background fill on the layer
- SurfaceFlinger.h: add WaylandSurface as friend for
  setTransactionState access

Change-Id: If00335b28ad3798ad531bae7c6a40fee88f5f6ab
---
 services/surfaceflinger/SurfaceFlinger.h      |  1 +
 .../Wayland/WaylandCompositor.cpp             | 18 +++-
 .../surfaceflinger/Wayland/WaylandSurface.cpp | 89 ++++++++-----------
 3 files changed, 55 insertions(+), 53 deletions(-)

